            <p>
                There are two verbs which are considered Class IV verbs but which differ from the regular pattern of most verbs in this class: '<em>niman - to take</em>'
                and '<em>cuman - to come</em>'. These are two commonly used verbs so it is important to 
                recognise them in all their forms. The vowel in both verbs becomes '<strong>o</strong>' in the past singular 
                and '<strong>o</strong>' in the past plural. 
            </p>
